    20  /** Custom error message or function to generate it */
    21  errorMessage?: string | ((error: string) => string)
    22  /** Callback fired on successful submission */
    23  onSuccess?: (result: TResult) => void
    24  /** Callback fired on submission error */
    25  onError?: (error: string) => void
    26  /** Transform form data before submission */
    27  transformFormData?: (data: TFormData) => Record<string, unknown>
    28  /** Whether to reset form on successful submission */
    29  resetOnSuccess?: boolean
    30  /** Whether to require CSRF token (default: true) */
    31  requireCsrf?: boolean
    32}
    33
    34interface SecureFormSubmissionResult<TFormData, TResult> {
    35  /** Whether the form is currently being submitted */
    36  isSubmitting: boolean
    37  /** Whether there's a pending debounced submission */
    38  isPending: boolean
    39  /** The current submission state from useActionState */
    40  submissionState: {
    41    success: boolean
    42    data: TResult | null
    43    error: string | null

    45  /** Submit handler for the form */

    47  /** Direct submission handler (bypasses debouncing) */
    48  handleDirectSubmit: (data: TFormData) => void
    49  /** Cancel any pending submission */
    50  cancelSubmission: () => void
    51  /** Reset submission state */
    52  resetSubmission: () => void
    53  /** Form action for use with form action attribute */
    54  formAction: (formData: FormData) => void
    55}
    56
    57export function useSecureFormSubmission<TFormData extends Record<string, unknown>, TResult extends Record<string, unknown>>({
    58  form,
    59  action,
    60  formId,
    61  debounceDelay = 300,
    62  showToasts = true,
    63  successMessage,
    64  errorMessage,
    65  onSuccess,
    66  onError,
    67  transformFormData,
    68  resetOnSuccess = false,
    69  requireCsrf = true,
    70}: UseSecureFormSubmissionOptions<TFormData, TResult>): SecureFormSubmissionResult<TFormData, TResult> {
    71
    72  const [isLocalSubmitting, setIsLocalSubmitting] = useState(false)
    73  const [isPending, setIsPending] = useState(false)
    74  const submissionIdRef = useRef<string | null>(null)

    76  // Get CSRF token from session
    77  const { token: csrfToken, loading: csrfLoading } = useCsrfToken()

     4/**
     5 * ScreeningResult interface matching database schema
     6 * Note: matchedEntities is a JSONB field that may be null/undefined or have incomplete data
     7 */
     8interface ScreeningResult {
     9  id: string
    10  merchantName: string | null
    11  businessType: string | null
    12  hasMatch: boolean
    13  matchScore: string | number | null
    14  status: 'completed' | 'pending' | 'failed'
    15  checkedAt: string
    16  // JSONB field from database - needs defensive handling
    17  matchedEntities?: Array<{
    18    primaryName: string
    19    entityType: string
    20    programs?: string[] | null
    21    lists?: string[] | null
    22    matchScore: number
    23    aliases?: string[] | null
    24    remarks?: string | null
    25  }> | null
    26}
    27
    28// Helper function to get API base URL
    29function getApiBaseUrl(): string {
    30  if (process.env['API_BASE_URL']) {
    31    return process.env['API_BASE_URL']
    32  }
    33
    34  // Development fallback
    35  if (process.env['NODE_ENV'] === 'development') {
    36    return 'http://localhost:3001'
    37  }
    38
    39  // Production should always have proper environment variables set
    40  throw new Error('API_BASE_URL must be configured in production')
    41}
    42
    43// Fetch recent screening results from the API
    44export async function getScreeningResults(limit: number = 10): Promise<ScreeningResult[]> {
    45  try {
    46    const { userId, getToken } = await auth()
    47
    48    // If not authenticated, return empty array (or mock data for development)
    49    if (!userId) {
    50      console.warn('No user authenticated - returning empty screening results')
    51      return []
    52    }
    53
    54    // Get the secure JWT access token from Clerk
    55    const accessToken = await getToken()
    56    if (!accessToken) {
    57      console.error('No access token from Clerk')
    58      return []
    59    }
    60
    61    const baseURL = getApiBaseUrl()
    62    const controller = new AbortController()
    63    const timeoutId = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 10000) // 10s timeout
    64
    65    const response = await fetch(`${baseURL}/api/ofac/screening/recent?limit=${limit}`, {
    66      headers: {
    67        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    68        'Authorization': `Bearer ${accessToken}`,
    69      },
    70      cache: 'no-store', // Always fetch fresh data
    71      signal: controller.signal,
    72    })
    73
    74    clearTimeout(timeoutId)
    75
    76    if (!response.ok) {
    77      console.error('Failed to fetch screening results:', response.status, response.statusText)
    78      return []
    79    }
    80
    81    const data = await response.json()
    82
    83    if (!data.success || !data.data) {
    84      console.error('Invalid response from screening API:', data)
